@startuml UEORMS_Full_Sequence_Diagram
!pragma teoz true
autonumber
hide footbox

actor Guest
actor Admin
actor Employee
actor Manager
actor "HR Manager" as HRM
actor "Finance Manager" as FinM
actor "Inventory Manager" as InvM
actor "Sales Manager" as SalesM
actor "Purchase Manager" as PurM
actor "Project Manager" as ProjM

boundary "Web/Mobile Client" as Client
control "Express API Layer\n(app.js route orchestration)" as API
control "Auth + RBAC\n(requireAuth / permission middleware)" as AuthRBAC
control "Subscription Entitlement\n(requireModuleEntitlement)" as Entitlement
control "Workflow Engine + Approval Service" as WF
control "Realtime Gateway\n(WebSocket /ws)" as RT
control "Notification Service" as Notify
control "Email Service + Queue" as Email
control "Billing Service" as Billing
entity "Stripe / Razorpay" as Gateway
control "Integration Service" as Integr
control "Integration Event Manager" as EventBus
control "Scheduler (cron jobs)" as Scheduler

control "Company + Branch Services" as Company
control "Users + Invite + Department + SystemOptions" as CoreAdmin
control "HR Service" as HR
control "Attendance Service" as Attend
control "Payroll + Disbursement Services" as Payroll
control "Finance + Accounting Services" as Finance
control "Inventory + Warehouse Services" as Inventory
control "Manufacturing Service" as Mfg
control "CRM Service" as CRM
control "Sales Service" as Sales
control "Purchase Service" as Purchase
control "AP Service" as AP
control "Projects + Team Services" as Projects
control "Timesheet Service" as Timesheet
control "Assets Services\n(asset/allocation/maintenance/depreciation)" as Assets
control "Documents Service" as Docs
control "Communication Service" as Comm
control "Reports + Reporting Services" as Reports
control "Data Import/Export Service" as DataIO

database "PostgreSQL via Prisma" as DB

== 1) Onboarding, Authentication, and Subscription ==
Guest -> Client : Register / Register+Checkout
Client -> API : POST /api/auth/register or /register/checkout
API -> Billing : fetch public plans / create pending registration
Billing -> DB : Plan, PendingRegistration, Subscription init
DB --> Billing : plan + registration context
Billing --> API : plan decision + payment context
API -> AuthRBAC : create tenant/admin user + hash password + issue JWT
AuthRBAC -> DB : Tenant, User, Role/UserRole inserts
DB --> AuthRBAC : user + tenant created
AuthRBAC --> API : token + identity
API -> Email : send welcome/verification
API --> Client : onboarding success + JWT

Guest -> Client : Login
Client -> API : POST /api/auth/login
API -> AuthRBAC : validate credentials + roles + permissions
AuthRBAC -> DB : User + RolePermission lookup
DB --> AuthRBAC : auth context
AuthRBAC --> API : JWT + claims
API --> Client : login success

Guest -> Client : Forgot password
Client -> API : POST /api/auth/forgot-password -> verify-otp -> reset-password
API -> AuthRBAC : OTP reset flow
AuthRBAC -> DB : PasswordReset + User update
API -> Email : send OTP mail
API --> Client : password reset completed

== 2) Core Admin Configuration ==
Admin -> Client : Configure company / branches / options / departments / users
Client -> API : /api/company, /api/branches, /api/system-options, /api/departments, /api/users
API -> AuthRBAC : auth + role/permission validation
AuthRBAC --> API : authorized
API -> Company : company setup, approval matrix, custom fields, branch CRUD
Company -> DB : CompanyConfig, ApprovalMatrix, CustomField, Branch
DB --> Company : persisted config
API -> CoreAdmin : user invite, role assignment, department/system option updates
CoreAdmin -> DB : UserInvite, UserRole, Department, SystemOption
CoreAdmin -> Email : invitation email
CoreAdmin --> API : admin configuration result
API --> Client : setup saved

== 3) Cross-Cutting Guard Flow (all secured modules) ==
Employee -> Client : Access module endpoint
Client -> API : any /api/{module}
API -> AuthRBAC : requireAuth + permission check
AuthRBAC --> API : user context
API -> Entitlement : verify module included in active subscription
Entitlement -> DB : Subscription + SubscriptionItem + Plan lookup
DB --> Entitlement : entitlement decision
Entitlement --> API : allowed / forbidden
API --> Client : proceed or 403

== 4) Workflow/Approval Pattern Used by Business Modules ==
Employee -> Client : Submit approval-based transaction
Client -> API : e.g. leave/expense/stock/requisition/timesheet request
API -> WF : create workflow request + first approval step
WF -> DB : WorkflowRequest + Approval (PENDING)
DB --> WF : approval chain state
WF -> Notify : notify approver queue
Notify -> DB : Notification insert
Notify -> RT : push approval event
WF --> API : request submitted
API --> Client : pending approval

Manager -> Client : Approve / Reject
Client -> API : POST /api/approvals/:id/approve|reject
API -> WF : resolve approval action
WF -> DB : Approval status + request status progression
alt approved and more steps
  WF -> DB : create next approval step
else approved final
  WF -> Notify : notify requester + downstream module completion
end
WF --> API : approval result
API --> Client : action completed

== 5) HR, Attendance, Payroll, Disbursement ==
HRM -> Client : Employee/Leave operations
Client -> API : /api/employees, /api/leave-types, /api/leave-requests
API -> HR : employee + leave service flows
HR -> DB : Employee, LeaveType, LeaveRequest, Task, WorkReport
DB --> HR : HR transaction data
HR -> WF : leave approval workflow trigger
WF -> Notify : approver + requester notifications
API --> Client : HR result

Employee -> Client : Clock in/out, view attendance
Client -> API : /api/attendance/clock-in, /clock-out, /reports
API -> Attend : time tracking, shifts, overtime, reports
Attend -> DB : Attendance, TimeTracking, ShiftAssignment, OvertimeRecord, AttendanceReport
Attend -> WF : overtime approval requests
Attend -> Notify : attendance/ot alerts
API --> Client : attendance status

HRM -> Client : Run payroll
Client -> API : /api/payroll/cycles, generate-payslips, disbursements
API -> Payroll : payroll cycle calculation + payslip generation
Payroll -> DB : PayrollCycle, Payslip, SalaryComponent, TaxConfiguration, SalaryDisbursement
Payroll -> WF : payslip/finance approvals where configured
Payroll -> Integr : sync payroll to GL
Integr -> EventBus : emit payroll:cycle:processed
EventBus -> Finance : payroll accounting sync trigger
Payroll -> Email : payslip/disbursement notices
Payroll --> API : payroll outputs
API --> Client : payroll completed

== 6) Finance and Accounting ==
Employee -> Client : Submit expense claim
Client -> API : /api/expense-claims
API -> Finance : create expense claim
Finance -> DB : ExpenseCategory, ExpenseClaim
Finance -> WF : expense approval request
WF -> Notify : finance approval queue
API --> Client : claim submitted

FinM -> Client : Accounting operations
Client -> API : /api/accounting/* + /api/finance-dashboard
API -> Finance : chart of accounts, journals, posting, reversals, dashboard
Finance -> DB : ChartOfAccounts, JournalEntry, JournalEntryLine, LedgerEntry, FiscalYear
Finance -> Reports : financial aggregates for dashboard
Finance --> API : accounting result
API --> Client : finance response

== 7) Inventory and Manufacturing ==
InvM -> Client : Manage items/warehouses/stock movement
Client -> API : /api/inventory, /api/warehouses, /api/stock-movements
API -> Inventory : item + warehouse + stock movement services
Inventory -> DB : Item, Warehouse, WarehouseStock, StockMovement, LotBatch
Inventory -> WF : approval for configured stock/item actions
Inventory -> RT : inventory update broadcast
Inventory -> Integr : sync inventory movement to GL
Integr -> EventBus : inventory:movement:completed
EventBus -> Finance : integration posting trigger
API --> Client : inventory result

InvM -> Client : Manufacturing execution
Client -> API : /api/manufacturing/bom and /work-orders
API -> Mfg : BOM, work order, operations, material issue/consume
Mfg -> DB : BillOfMaterials, BOMItem, WorkOrder, WorkOrderOperation, WorkOrderMaterial, ProductionBatch
Mfg -> Integr : sync manufacturing cost to GL
Integr -> EventBus : manufacturing:workorder:completed
EventBus -> Finance : manufacturing accounting sync
API --> Client : manufacturing result

== 8) CRM and Sales ==
SalesM -> Client : CRM lifecycle
Client -> API : /api/crm/customers contacts leads deals pipelines activities attachments communications
API -> CRM : customer lifecycle + pipeline + activity orchestration
CRM -> DB : Customer, Contact, Lead, Deal, Pipeline, PipelineStage, Activity, Attachment, Communication, Tag
CRM -> Notify : reminders/overdue/upcoming activity notifications
CRM --> API : CRM result
API --> Client : CRM updated

SalesM -> Client : Sales lifecycle
Client -> API : /api/sales/quotations orders invoices trackings payments analytics
API -> Sales : quotation->order->invoice conversions and tracking
Sales -> DB : SalesQuotation, SalesOrder, SalesInvoice, InvoicePayment, SalesOrderTracking
Sales -> Integr : sync sales order completion to AR/GL
Integr -> EventBus : sales:order:completed
EventBus -> Finance : revenue posting sync
Sales -> Reports : sales analytics/forecast/export jobs
Sales --> API : sales output
API --> Client : sales completed

== 9) Purchase and Accounts Payable ==
PurM -> Client : Procurement lifecycle
Client -> API : /api/purchase/vendors requisitions orders receipts evaluations analytics
API -> Purchase : requisition->PO->receipt workflows
Purchase -> DB : Vendor, PurchaseRequisition, PurchaseOrder, GoodsReceipt, SupplierEvaluation
Purchase -> WF : requisition/PO approvals
Purchase -> Inventory : stock updates on receipt
Purchase -> Integr : AP/GL sync on receipt/invoice
Integr -> EventBus : purchase:order:received
EventBus -> AP : AP sync trigger
API --> Client : purchase result

FinM -> Client : AP operations
Client -> API : /api/ap/bills payments aging vendor statement
API -> AP : bill lifecycle + three-way match + payments
AP -> DB : APBill, Payment
AP -> WF : bill approval chain
AP -> Finance : payable postings
AP -> Notify : due/overdue reminders
API --> Client : AP result

== 10) Projects and Timesheets ==
ProjM -> Client : Project operations
Client -> API : /api/projects + members + dashboard
API -> Projects : project/milestone/resource/budget/team capacity
Projects -> DB : Project, ProjectMember, ProjectMilestone, ProjectMilestoneDependency, ProjectResource, ProjectBudget, ProjectTimeLog
Projects --> API : project outputs
API --> Client : project updated

Employee -> Client : Timesheet entry and submission
Client -> API : /api/timesheets
API -> Timesheet : create/update/submit/approve/reject flows
Timesheet -> DB : ProjectTimesheet
Timesheet -> WF : timesheet approval steps
Timesheet -> Notify : approver + employee notifications
API --> Client : timesheet status

== 11) Assets, Documents, Communication ==
Employee -> Client : Asset operations
Client -> API : /api/assets, /api/asset-allocations, /api/asset-maintenance, /api/asset-depreciation
API -> Assets : asset CRUD, allocation/return, maintenance, depreciation
Assets -> DB : AssetCategory, Asset, AssetAllocation, AssetMaintenance, AssetDepreciation
Assets -> Scheduler : overdue allocation checks
Scheduler -> Notify : overdue alerts
Scheduler -> Email : overdue notification emails
API --> Client : asset result

Employee -> Client : Document operations
Client -> API : /api/documents/*
API -> Docs : folders, docs, versions, templates, shares, permissions, activities
Docs -> DB : DocumentFolder, Document, DocumentVersion, DocumentTemplate, DocumentShare, DocumentPermission, DocumentFolderPermission, DocumentActivity, DocumentComment
Docs -> Notify : share/permission notifications
API --> Client : document result

Employee -> Client : Messaging/announcements/channels/email templates
Client -> API : /api/communication/*
API -> Comm : conversations, messages, reactions, announcements, channels, email logs/queue
Comm -> DB : Conversation, ConversationParticipant, Message, MessageReaction, MessageReadReceipt, Announcement, AnnouncementRead, ChatChannel, ChatChannelMember, EmailTemplate, EmailLog, EmailQueue
Comm -> RT : live message/typing/read/reaction broadcast
Comm -> Email : queued email dispatch
API --> Client : communication result

== 12) Reporting, Import/Export, and Integration API ==
FinM -> Client : Reports and analytics
Client -> API : /api/reports and /api/reporting
API -> Reports : financial/hr/inventory/custom/scheduled reports
Reports -> DB : ReportTemplate, Report, ReportSchedule + source domain tables
Reports -> DataIO : export pipeline (pdf/excel/csv)
Reports --> API : report payload/files
API --> Client : report response

Admin -> Client : Bulk import/export
Client -> API : /api/data/import/* and /api/data/export/*
API -> DataIO : parse/validate/import or export templates/data
DataIO -> DB : upsert/query operational tables
DataIO --> API : import/export results
API --> Client : data utility response

Admin -> Client : Manual integration controls
Client -> API : /api/integration/sync-* /status /config /batch-sync
API -> Integr : cross-module sync actions
Integr -> DB : integration read/write + status
Integr -> EventBus : emit integration lifecycle events
Integr --> API : sync status
API --> Client : integration response

== 13) Subscription Webhooks and External Billing ==
Gateway -> API : POST /api/billing/webhooks/stripe|razorpay
API -> Billing : validate signature/event + idempotency check
Billing -> DB : BillingEvent find/create/update
alt event not processed
  Billing -> DB : update subscription/payment state
  Billing -> Notify : subscription/billing notification
  Billing -> Email : invoice email / failure notice
else already processed
  Billing --> API : idempotent ack
end
API --> Gateway : webhook acknowledged

== 14) Realtime and Scheduled System Activities ==
Client -> RT : connect /ws?token=JWT and subscribe endpoints
RT -> AuthRBAC : token verify + user resolve
AuthRBAC -> DB : user/tenant lookup
RT --> Client : connected + live stream

Scheduler -> Assets : midnight overdue allocation scan
Assets -> DB : find and mark overdue allocations
Assets -> Notify : create overdue notifications
Assets -> Email : send overdue emails

Scheduler -> Attend : end-of-day absent marking
Attend -> DB : create ABSENT records when no attendance + no approved leave

== 15) Unified Observability ==
API -> DB : write AuditLog for critical actions
Notify -> DB : persist notifications/read states
RT --> Client : dashboard/activity/module realtime updates

@enduml
